====Trivia====
This is one of only three everyday kanji with a 5 morae reading, and one of only two nouns, namely {{term|志|tr=こころざし, kokorozashi|lang=ja}} (nominalization of form of verb {{term|志す|tr=こころざす, kokorozasu|lang=ja}}, which has a 4 morae reading). The only other kanji with a 5 morae reading are {{term|承|lang=ja}}, in the verb {{term|承る|tr=（うけたまわ）る, uketamawa-ru|lang=ja}}, and {{term|詔||tr=みことのり, mikotonori|lang=ja}}, and no everyday kanji have a 6 or more morae reading.

The unusually long reading is due to two factors: 志 is a nominalization of the verb 志す which has a long reading (4 morae, ''kokoroza-su''), which itself is a noun-verb compound, 心指す ''kokoro-za(su)''. The nominalization removing the okurigana, hence increasing the reading by one morae, yielding 4+1=5, or more finely 3+(1+1)=5 (compare common {{term|話|tr=はなし, hanashi|lang=ja}} 2+1=3, from {{term|話す|tr=はなす, hana-su|lang=ja}}).

